cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with fine-grained recognition, which is a task within computer vision. It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it involves deep learning techniques and the development of a novel architecture for representation learning. Multimedia (cs.MM) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) are also possible sub-categories as the paper involves the use of convolutional filters and the training of a neural network.
